a 1631","Beerfelden, Odenwaldkreis, Hessen, Germany":"Beerfelden, Odenwaldkreis, Hessen, Duitsland","of Beerfelden, Erbach, Starkenburg, Hessen-Darmstadt":"Beerfelden, Kreis Erbach, Großherzogtum Hessen","Beerfelden, Odenwaldkreis, Hessen, Deutschland":"Beerfelden, Odenwaldkreis, Hessen, Duitsland"},"en":{"1595–after 1631":"1595–after 1631","1595–1631":"1595–1631","1600–1640":"1600–1640","–1626":"–1626","–Female":"Deceased","1624–1688":"1624–1688","1560–1617":"1560–1617","1562–1618":"1562–1618","January 11, 1623 ":"11 January 1623","after 1618":"after 1618","1560":"1560","ABT 1624":"about 1624","1624":"1624","1688":"1688","1600":"1600","1631":"1631","1640":"1640","1595":"1595","1562":"1562","1618":"1618","1617":"1617","about 1594":"about 1594","1626":"1626","after 1631":"after 1631","Beerfelden, Odenwaldkreis, Hessen, Germany":"Beerfelden, Odenwaldkreis, Hesse, Germany","of Beerfelden, Erbach, Starkenburg, Hessen-Darmstadt":"Beerfelden, Erbach, Grand Duchy of Hesse","Beerfelden, Odenwaldkreis, Hessen, Deutschland":"Beerfelden, Odenwaldkreis, Hesse, Germany","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Kumpf","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Hermann, Kurt, Otto.","German: nickname for a short stout man, from Middle High German <i>kumpf</i> ‘(small) measure of grain, pouch (for a whetstone)’. Compare   Kump  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Kump","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Erwin, Mathias, Alois, Gerhard, Traude.","German: metonymic occupational name for a bowl maker, from Middle Low German <i>kump</i> ‘(wooden) bowl’.","German: habitational name from a place so named in Westphalia."]}]},{"name":"Peter","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of the name of the best-known of all Christ's apostles, traditionally regarded as the founder of the Christian Church. The name derives, via Latin, from Greek <i>petros</i> ‘stone, rock’. This is used as a translation of the Aramaic byname <i>Cephas</i>, given to the apostle  Simon  son of Jona, to distinguish him from another of the same name (  Simon Zelotes ). ‘When Jesus beheld him, he said, Thou art Simon the son of Jona: thou shalt be called Cephas, which is by interpretation, A stone’ (John 1:42). According to Matthew 16:17–18, Christ says more explicitly, ‘Blessed art thou, Simon Bar-jona … thou art Peter, and upon this rock I will build my church’. The name has been in continuous use since the Middle Ages."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Peter Kumpf was born in 1595, in Beerfelden, Odenwaldkreis, Hesse, Germany, his father, Hanß Michael Kumpft, was 36 and his mother, Margaretha, was 34. He married Elisabeth Zeller on 11 January 1623, in Beerfelden, Odenwaldkreis, Hesse, Germany. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died after 1631, in his hometown."},"et":{"1595–after 1631":"1595–pärast 1631","1595–1631":"1595–1631","1600–1640":"1600–1640","–1626":"–1626","–Female":"Surnud","1624–1688":"1624–1688","1560–1617":"1560–1617","1562–1618":"1562–1618","January 11, 1623 ":"11. jaanuar 1623","after 1618":"pärast 1618","1560":"1560","ABT 1624":"umbes 1624","1624":"1624","1688":"1688","1600":"1600","1631":"1631","1640":"1640","1595":"1595","1562":"1562","1618":"1618","1617":"1617","about 1594":"umbes 1594","1626":"1626","after 1631":"pärast 1631","Beerfelden, Odenwaldkreis, Hessen, Germany":"Beerfelden, Odenwaldkreis, Hessen, Saksamaa","of Beerfelden, Erbach, Starkenburg, Hessen-Darmstadt":"Beerfelden, Kreis Erbach, Großherzogtum Hessen","Beerfelden, Odenwaldkreis, Hessen, Deutschland":"Beerfelden, Odenwaldkreis, Hessen, Saksamaa"},"fi":{"1595–after 1631":"1595–1631 jälkeen","1595–1631":"1595–1631","1600–1640":"1600–1640","–1626":"–1626","–Female":"Kuollut","1624–1688":"1624–1688","1560–1617":"1560–1617","1562–1618":"1562–1618","January 11, 1623 ":"11. tammikuuta 1623","after 1618":"1618